# Internationalization (slang)

## Source files

```
lib/i18n/
├── strings.i18n.json       # English base (or strings_en)
├── strings_de.i18n.json    # Locale overrides
└── strings.g.dart          # Generated — do not edit
```

## Workflow

1. Add/edit keys in JSON — nested objects, **camelCase** keys.
2. Run `dart run slang` or `scripts/codegen.sh`.
3. Use in UI: `Text(t.section.myKey)` — import `strings.g.dart`.

## Guidelines

- Every user-facing string goes through slang — no hardcoded labels in widgets.
- Keep keys organized by screen/feature (`settings`, `libraries`, `playback`, …).
- Concise copy — TV layouts truncate aggressively.
- Pluralization / parameters — follow slang docs via Context7 when needed.

## Adding a locale

1. Copy English JSON structure to `strings_<locale>.i18n.json`.
2. Translate values only — preserve key structure.
3. Run codegen; verify `strings_<locale>.g.dart` generated.

## Forbidden

- Hand-editing `strings*.g.dart`
- User-visible English literals in `lib/screens/` or `lib/widgets/`
- Breaking key paths without updating all locale files
